Vice President Yemi Osinbajo has visited the Olubadan of Ibadan, Oba Olalekan Balogun, at his Alarere Palace in Ibadan of Friday. The VP left the Olubadan palace around 11:30 am. His visit to the traditional ruler preceded a meeting with his presidential support groups in the state. Shortly after the meeting with the Olubadan, Osinbajo proceeded to the Ibadan Civic Center where he is meeting with the support groups. At the meeting, a minute silence was observed for three former governors of Oyo State, Lam Adesina, Isiaka Ajimobi and Otunba Adebayo Alao-Akala. Dignitaries at the event include Chief Osunbor, Senator Teslim Folarin, Chief Niyi Akintola, Senator Bulkachuwa, Babafemi Ojudu, and Oyo State Chairman of the All Progressives Congress, Isaac Omodewu. Details later.  YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE Buhari Urges MTN For Quality Service, Downward Price Review In Cost Of Data, Other Services President Muhammadu Buhari Friday at State House Abuja urged the MTN Group to make the available top-of-the-range service to its Nigerian subscribers… We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state…  Osinbajo in Ibadan, visits Olubadan  Osinbajo in Ibadan, visits Olubadan  Osinbajo in Ibadan, visits Olubadan  Osinbajo in Ibadan, visits Olubadan Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report…